15/04/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Ministry Chief Secretary General Boyko Borissov said Wednesday (14 April) that the ministry's security plan for the Summer Olympics in Athens requires additional funds. 
Youth and Sports Minister Vassil Ivanov pledged his support for securing the extra 5m leva needed.
In other news Wednesday, NATO Allied Air Forces Southern Europe Commander Lieutenant General Glen W. 
Moorhead III visited the Graf Ignatievo 3rd Fighter Airbase, where he attended an air force drill. 
Moorhead reportedly praised air force readiness. 
Bulgaria formally joined the Alliance on 29 March. 
(BTA, BNR, bTV, BNT - 14/04/04)
